Class amuse.data.Feature extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: 9197405714295877274L

Serialized Fields

ids

java.util.ArrayList<E> ids
For a raw feature only one id exists; if a processed feature is calculated based on different features (e.g. after PCA), all ids of required raw features are saved here. This information can be used e.g. for calculation of pruning ratio

extractorId

int extractorId

dimension

int dimension
Dimension of this feature (e.g. linear prediction coefficients may have a dimension equal to 10

sourceFrameSize

int sourceFrameSize
Time window size in samples, from which the feature was extracted, e.g. 512 samples

history

java.util.ArrayList<E> history
For processed features, here the performed steps are saved. First step = original name of the feature

values

java.util.ArrayList<E> values

windows

java.util.ArrayList<E> windows

description

java.lang.String description
Description of this feature

isSelectedForExtraction

boolean isSelectedForExtraction
This value is used to determine if this feature is selected for extraction

Package amuse.nodes.optimizer

Class amuse.nodes.optimizer.OptimizationConfiguration extends TaskConfiguration implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: -6880712656836146853L

Serialized Fields

categoryLearningId

java.lang.Integer categoryLearningId
Category Id for training set (only from these files the training models will be built)

categoryOptimizationId

java.lang.Integer categoryOptimizationId
Category Id for optimization set. Set to -1 if optimization should be done as 10-fold cross-validation using only the training set

categoryTestId

java.lang.Integer categoryTestId
Category Id for independent test set (Here the generalization performance of optimizer can be evaluated). Set to -1 if independent test set should not be used

algorithmDescription

java.lang.String algorithmDescription
ID of optimization algorithm from optimizerAlgorithmTable.arff (optionally with parameters listed in brackets)

continueOldExperimentFrom

java.lang.String continueOldExperimentFrom
For a new experiment set to -1. If the previous optimization should be continued, set here the path to the log file with previous experiment

destinationFolder

java.lang.String destinationFolder
Folder for optimization results: they are written to the following folder: '[optimizationDatabase from amuse.properties]/[evaluation category description]/ DESTINATION_FOLDER/optimization_x.arff' where x is equal to the number of files in the folder plus one
